WEBVTT

00:05.296 --> 00:06.172
<i>[blues music playing]</i>

00:08.299 --> 00:12.512
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:12.512 --> 00:15.306
- Hey, guys. What's up?
- Hey.

00:15.306 --> 00:16.891
- Hey.
- Hey.

00:16.891 --> 00:24.065
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:27.736 --> 00:29.863
Hank, you are not gonna
believe what I found.

00:29.863 --> 00:31.197
Huh.

00:31.197 --> 00:33.074
I was cleaning out
the back room for Bob.

00:33.074 --> 00:34.492
- Yeah?
- Man hasn't touched the place

00:34.492 --> 00:37.203
in 40 years.

00:37.203 --> 00:40.498
Found this
stuck to an old receipt.

00:40.498 --> 00:42.667
Oh.

00:42.667 --> 00:44.336
I didn't know Justin
ever worked here.

00:44.336 --> 00:47.589
Yeah, summer 2010.

00:47.589 --> 00:51.051
Bob let him work behind the bar
a few weeks when he turned 21.

00:51.051 --> 00:53.219
He liked it.

00:53.219 --> 00:55.638
Didn't last long?

00:55.638 --> 00:57.599
Nah.

00:57.599 --> 00:58.808
Nah, keep it.

00:58.808 --> 01:00.352
He looks real happy there.

01:00.352 --> 01:01.895
Before everything.

01:01.895 --> 01:03.563
It's yours.

01:05.482 --> 01:06.900
Thanks.

01:06.900 --> 01:13.823
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:25.043 --> 01:28.129
[faint high-pitched beeping]

01:33.301 --> 01:36.262
[beeping grows louder]

01:36.262 --> 01:38.932
<i>[tense music]</i>

01:38.932 --> 01:45.855
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:00.286 --> 02:03.456
[cat meows]

02:42.162 --> 02:43.163
<i>[knocking]</i>

02:43.163 --> 02:44.330
Police.

02:44.330 --> 02:45.665
I need to see your cameras.

02:45.665 --> 02:47.334
Is this about
that robbery I filed?

02:47.334 --> 02:49.961
- When was that?
- Then I guess not.

02:49.961 --> 02:51.296
It was over a month ago.

02:51.296 --> 02:53.131
It's the third one
I reported this year.

02:53.131 --> 02:54.341
Right, that's not
why I'm here,

02:54.341 --> 02:56.468
but I do need to see
your cameras.

02:56.468 --> 02:58.553
Of course, let me help you.

03:00.764 --> 03:01.723
Back here.

03:03.641 --> 03:06.561
Help yourself.
- Thank you.

03:06.561 --> 03:08.271
And I don't know how to make
the footage any clearer.

03:08.271 --> 03:10.565
And no, I don't have
another angle, so.

03:35.799 --> 03:42.597
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:12.711 --> 04:13.378
Yes.
And I want photos

04:14.462 --> 04:16.256
of the blood spatter
in every size.

04:16.256 --> 04:17.841
Put a rush on it. Use Greggins.

04:17.841 --> 04:19.217
He's the best.
- Okay. Come on.

04:19.217 --> 04:20.427
The BOLO's out.

04:20.427 --> 04:21.845
Ford Taurus was hot.

04:21.845 --> 04:23.972
Check local chop shops,
salvage yards.

04:23.972 --> 04:25.432
We might get lucky
if the offender tries

04:25.432 --> 04:27.100
to ditch the vehicle.
Go.

04:27.100 --> 04:29.853
Car owner reported the theft.
No footage of it yet.

04:29.853 --> 04:31.604
Ruzek's uploading the footage
from the convenience store,

04:31.604 --> 04:33.648
and he's rushing facial rec.
- Okay. Witnesses?

04:33.648 --> 04:35.150
Knock-and-talks
are happening right now.

04:35.150 --> 04:36.776
Sarge! Hey, Sarge!

04:36.776 --> 04:38.611
Found these under the dumpster.

04:38.611 --> 04:40.238
It's possible it fell
from the victim's hand,

04:40.238 --> 04:41.364
maybe his pocket
when he was attacked.

04:41.364 --> 04:43.575
Huh. Party drugs.

04:43.575 --> 04:44.826
Kid might have just bought.

04:44.826 --> 04:46.327
All right,
run them through the lab.

04:46.327 --> 04:47.871
Loop in Narcotics,
see what they know.

04:47.871 --> 04:49.164
Right.

04:49.164 --> 04:50.874
Boss, got a hit
on facial rec.

04:50.874 --> 04:54.127
Kid's name, Noah Gorman,
19 years old.

04:54.127 --> 04:55.920
No LKA in Chicago.

04:55.920 --> 04:58.173
Ah, just graduated
high school last year.

04:58.173 --> 05:00.133
Marion, Indiana.

05:00.133 --> 05:01.801
Doesn't seem like he's been
in the city very long.

05:01.801 --> 05:02.927
All right,
well, you head up the scene.

05:02.927 --> 05:05.597
Start digging into Noah.
- Yeah.

05:05.597 --> 05:07.307
All right, get me
his parents' contact info.

05:07.307 --> 05:09.642
I'm gonna notify them myself.
- Right.

05:12.187 --> 05:13.688
Ma'am.

05:15.482 --> 05:16.858
Yes, that is your right.

05:16.858 --> 05:18.360
But your son--

05:22.947 --> 05:24.449
Mm-hmm.

05:26.201 --> 05:27.619
Right.

05:30.413 --> 05:33.541
No, I think I understand.

05:33.541 --> 05:35.710
Yeah. Goodbye.

05:46.721 --> 05:49.891
Just got off the phone
with Noah's family in Indiana.

05:51.851 --> 05:56.106
They said this is what happens
when you live a life of sin.

05:56.106 --> 05:57.148
Well, what's that mean?

05:59.859 --> 06:01.945
Noah came out as gay
two months ago.

06:01.945 --> 06:04.864
They kicked him out.

06:04.864 --> 06:06.908
They said they
won't be needing updates

06:06.908 --> 06:10.203
on the abduction as
Noah is no longer their son.

06:10.203 --> 06:11.538
Whoa.

06:18.586 --> 06:20.171
All right, he's been missing
three hours.

06:20.171 --> 06:21.381
Tell me we have something.

06:21.381 --> 06:23.258
No hits on the BOLO yet.

06:23.258 --> 06:24.718
Okay. Noah himself?

06:24.718 --> 06:26.594
Seems to fit with
what his parents told you.

06:26.594 --> 06:29.139
Noah took a bus into Chicago
two months ago,

06:29.139 --> 06:32.892
but we've got no hits on
shelters, hotels, hostels.

06:32.892 --> 06:34.310
We have no idea
where he's laying his head.

06:34.310 --> 06:36.563
Yeah, and the kid's got no
active credit cards,

06:36.563 --> 06:38.023
no current cell phone, either.

06:38.023 --> 06:39.691
No friends or family
in the city.

06:39.691 --> 06:41.151
It seems like he's all alone
out here.

06:41.151 --> 06:42.944
Got something good
from Narcotics.

06:42.944 --> 06:46.698
The lab ID'd the drugs as MDMA
laced with meth.

06:46.698 --> 06:50.410
The man who deals in that area
is Zach "ZJ" Jones.

06:50.410 --> 06:52.662
He deals in red octagon pills

06:52.662 --> 06:55.081
and is known for abducting
and torturing clients

06:55.081 --> 06:56.166
who stiff him.

06:56.166 --> 06:57.584
- Seriously?
- Yeah.

06:57.584 --> 06:59.085
He's suspected of doing it
four times

06:59.085 --> 07:00.754
but was only arrested twice
for kidnapping

07:00.754 --> 07:02.130
and unlawful restraint.

07:02.130 --> 07:04.424
But managed to get out
of both cases pre-trial.

07:04.424 --> 07:06.009
- How close is it?
- Almost exact.

07:06.009 --> 07:08.094
Jones's stats match
our offender stats

07:08.094 --> 07:09.512
in the video to a T.

07:09.512 --> 07:11.431
The MO matches the previous
four abductions.

07:11.431 --> 07:14.142
And Jones's prints were found
on the baggie of drugs

07:14.142 --> 07:15.268
at the scene.

07:15.268 --> 07:16.936
He practically left us
a calling card.

07:16.936 --> 07:18.605
I went to his house,
the place looks empty.

07:18.605 --> 07:20.982
Hit the door now.

07:20.982 --> 07:22.317
Hey, Sarge.

07:22.317 --> 07:24.110
One more thing,
Chapman was the lead prosecutor

07:24.110 --> 07:25.236
on both previous cases.

07:33.078 --> 07:34.996
Team is there now.
Jones isn't home.

07:34.996 --> 07:37.540
I'm not surprised.
Man thinks he's smart.

07:37.540 --> 07:38.958
He will be dodging the police.

07:38.958 --> 07:40.794
Okay, what technicalities
are we talking?

07:40.794 --> 07:43.254
He claims illegal search
on one,

07:43.254 --> 07:46.049
and the next was a bad victim,
drug user.

07:46.049 --> 07:50.095
And Jones's scumbag of a lawyer
dug up some skeletons

07:50.095 --> 07:51.554
and the victim recanted.

07:51.554 --> 07:53.056
But there was never any doubt

07:53.056 --> 07:54.724
Jones was our man
in both cases.

07:54.724 --> 07:56.643
So we'll make it
foolproof this time.

07:56.643 --> 07:58.395
We find Noah,
make it airtight together.

07:58.395 --> 08:01.856
Hank, do you see my desk?

08:01.856 --> 08:03.525
Are any of these
a current missing?

08:03.525 --> 08:06.986
No, but half of these have
been personally handed to me.

08:06.986 --> 08:10.031
Your bosses give you
a pep talk too?

08:10.031 --> 08:12.033
Our close rate's
not where it should be.

08:12.033 --> 08:13.952
Then work cases
you can close.

08:13.952 --> 08:17.247
I don't get to work in my
own personal vacuum like you.

08:17.247 --> 08:19.624
I would like to keep my job.

08:22.335 --> 08:23.795
Nina, the kid's 19.

08:23.795 --> 08:25.672
He's just a child.

08:25.672 --> 08:28.299
You know what
his family told me?

08:28.299 --> 08:29.801
They said this is his fault

08:29.801 --> 08:32.178
because he denounced God
by being gay.

08:32.178 --> 08:35.515
No one else
reported him missing.

08:35.515 --> 08:37.726
There's no one looking for him.

08:39.811 --> 08:41.563
We're all he's got.

08:50.238 --> 08:52.699
Jones's MO
is always the same.

08:52.699 --> 08:54.701
He abducts customers
who don't pay.

08:54.701 --> 08:56.703
Usually,
he uses a stolen vehicle,

08:56.703 --> 08:58.747
takes them
to a private location,

08:58.747 --> 09:01.124
and then uses a tack hammer
to break their kneecaps.

09:01.124 --> 09:02.792
- So it's a message.
- Yeah.

09:02.792 --> 09:04.377
Don't ever stiff him.

09:04.377 --> 09:06.296
Usually holds them
for about 10 hours,

09:06.296 --> 09:08.173
and then he brings them
to a public location

09:08.173 --> 09:11.259
and makes them crawl to safety.
- Hmm.

09:11.259 --> 09:13.428
The last victim almost bled out
before he was found.

09:13.428 --> 09:15.096
Wow.
- And you never uncovered

09:15.096 --> 09:16.723
where he holds them?
- No.

09:16.723 --> 09:19.225
Victims refuse to talk
out of fear.

09:19.225 --> 09:21.186
Okay, so we may not know
where he held them,

09:21.186 --> 09:22.645
but we do know
where he dropped them.

09:22.645 --> 09:24.064
Same place he deals.

09:24.064 --> 09:26.191
Three of the last four
were found at Sweeney Park.

09:26.191 --> 09:27.067
I'll hit Sweeney Park.

09:27.067 --> 09:28.401
Torres, Upton, you're with me.

09:28.401 --> 09:30.111
Rest of you, keep digging.

09:30.111 --> 09:33.114
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

09:33.114 --> 09:36.159
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:36.159 --> 09:37.410
Still got no activity.

09:37.410 --> 09:38.453
<i>Copy that.</i>

09:38.453 --> 09:40.205
All quiet here.

09:40.205 --> 09:41.414
Just keep circling.

09:41.414 --> 09:43.583
<i>I'm gonna take
another pass around.</i>

09:43.583 --> 09:50.256
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:50.256 --> 09:52.092
One of Jones's clients?

09:52.092 --> 09:53.927
Yep.

09:53.927 --> 09:56.930
All right, take it.

09:56.930 --> 09:58.223
Hey, Voight, hang tight.

09:58.223 --> 10:00.141
We may have something.

10:00.141 --> 10:02.435
We're approaching now.
<i>- Copy.</i>

10:02.435 --> 10:05.438
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

10:05.438 --> 10:12.404
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:15.699 --> 10:17.117
What's good here, bro?

10:17.117 --> 10:18.993
- This ain't a party, man.
- Hey, no.

10:18.993 --> 10:21.079
I'm just looking
to pick up, man.

10:21.079 --> 10:24.624
My boy says this is a spot
for good ice.

10:24.624 --> 10:26.918
You got cash?

10:26.918 --> 10:30.380
Yeah, I got cash.
[sniffs]

10:30.380 --> 10:31.923
ZJ's your man,
north side of the park.

10:31.923 --> 10:34.467
But don't tell him I sent you.

10:34.467 --> 10:37.679
Thanks, bro.

10:37.679 --> 10:39.264
Sarge, I got a tweaker
says Jones

10:39.264 --> 10:40.640
is on the north side
of the park.

10:40.640 --> 10:41.850
I'm heading back
your way right now.

10:41.850 --> 10:44.185
Copy you.

10:47.063 --> 10:49.649
I got eyes on Jones
north side of the parking lot.

10:49.649 --> 10:50.900
He's moving to his vehicle.

10:50.900 --> 10:52.110
Get over here now.

10:55.238 --> 10:57.282
Chicago PD.

10:57.282 --> 10:58.742
Hey, wouldn't do that.

10:58.742 --> 11:05.874
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:09.169 --> 11:10.837
- Up. Get up.
- Okay. Okay.

11:10.837 --> 11:12.005
Got anything
that can hurt me?

11:12.005 --> 11:14.507
Got anything that can hurt me?

11:14.507 --> 11:15.633
Where's Noah?

11:15.633 --> 11:17.844
You drop him here?

11:17.844 --> 11:19.971
Where is he? Where's Noah?

11:19.971 --> 11:22.057
Noah? Who's that?

11:22.057 --> 11:23.391
Keep searching the park.

11:23.391 --> 11:25.060
Let's go.

11:30.106 --> 11:31.232
We scoured that entire park
for Noah Gorman,

11:32.609 --> 11:34.486
didn't find him.

11:34.486 --> 11:35.695
Where is he?

11:35.695 --> 11:37.739
Do I need to speak clear?

11:37.739 --> 11:39.324
I don't know anybody
by that name.

11:39.324 --> 11:41.659
You're sure smiling at me
like you know something.

11:41.659 --> 11:43.870
I know lots, cop.

11:43.870 --> 11:46.331
But nothing I'm gonna tell you.

11:46.331 --> 11:48.917
Where were you last night,
10:15 p.m.?

11:48.917 --> 11:50.502
Hmm.

11:50.502 --> 11:52.921
I was... driving.

11:52.921 --> 11:54.339
- Driving?
- Yeah.

11:54.339 --> 11:57.384
That is a really bad alibi.

11:57.384 --> 11:59.719
We already know Noah
had your drugs on him.

11:59.719 --> 12:01.346
- My drugs?
- Mm-hmm.

12:01.346 --> 12:02.847
I don't got no drugs.

12:02.847 --> 12:05.934
I don't sell no drugs.
- No. No.

12:05.934 --> 12:09.229
We got a witness and he's
ready to testify that you do.

12:09.229 --> 12:11.731
We got your fingerprints
on a bag of pills

12:11.731 --> 12:13.733
that belongs to Noah.

12:13.733 --> 12:15.860
And we got footage.

12:18.113 --> 12:20.240
That's you.

12:20.240 --> 12:21.533
Where's Noah Gorman?

12:21.533 --> 12:23.702
[chuckling]

12:23.702 --> 12:24.744
That ain't me.

12:24.744 --> 12:26.413
Where is he?

12:26.413 --> 12:28.915
Looks like he's in trouble.

12:30.125 --> 12:33.795
Well, you tell me where,
we will deal.

12:33.795 --> 12:36.715
- Lawyer.
- Something went wrong, hmm?

12:36.715 --> 12:38.633
You had to drop him
someplace else this time.

12:38.633 --> 12:41.594
Lawyer, lawyer,
lawyer, lawyer,

12:41.594 --> 12:45.765
lawyer, lawyer, lawyer,

12:45.765 --> 12:48.768
lawyer, lawyer, lawyer.

12:48.768 --> 12:49.936
[door shuts]

12:51.813 --> 12:53.648
You wanna give me
something to wipe that

12:53.648 --> 12:55.400
smile off his face?

12:55.400 --> 12:56.443
That's his playbook.

12:56.443 --> 12:57.944
Thinks he's invincible.

12:57.944 --> 13:00.572
He's gonna stall until
his bulldog lawyer shows up

13:00.572 --> 13:02.991
and then they're gonna
backstop that alibi somehow.

13:02.991 --> 13:05.368
Hey, start looking
for technicalities now.

13:05.368 --> 13:06.870
We're not giving him any.

13:06.870 --> 13:09.456
All right, 17 hours in,
tell me we have something.

13:09.456 --> 13:11.499
Not at the park.
Sweeney, all nearby streets,

13:11.499 --> 13:12.792
they were clear.

13:12.792 --> 13:14.794
No sign of Noah.
- We towed Jones's SUV here.

13:14.794 --> 13:16.171
No visible signs of blood yet.

13:16.171 --> 13:18.548
No mask inside, no pipe,
no evidence.

13:18.548 --> 13:20.091
Nothing at Jones's house.

13:20.091 --> 13:21.509
No sign Noah was ever there.

13:21.509 --> 13:24.137
All right, where are we at
with known associates?

13:24.137 --> 13:25.972
Still running.
Chapman's investigative team

13:25.972 --> 13:27.265
is helping, but nothing yet.

13:27.265 --> 13:28.975
What about the tweaker
from the park?

13:28.975 --> 13:30.393
He's not talking.

13:30.393 --> 13:32.437
Hey, we got a hit
on that investigative alert.

13:32.437 --> 13:34.314
Patrol spotted the car
used in the abduction

13:34.314 --> 13:36.608
going southbound on Fifth
at a high rate of speed.

13:36.608 --> 13:37.776
- It's moving now?
- Yeah.

13:37.776 --> 13:38.651
You think somebody's
dumping it?

13:38.651 --> 13:39.736
Or moving Noah.

13:39.736 --> 13:41.363
Tell him we're
joining pursuit.

13:41.363 --> 13:45.075
<i>[tense music]</i>

13:45.075 --> 13:47.327
<i>Offender vehicle approaching
the 1400 block of Fifth.</i>

13:47.327 --> 13:49.204
<i>Vehicle turned west
onto Masconomet.</i>

13:51.206 --> 13:52.791
<i>Offender vehicle
just crossed three lanes.</i>

13:52.791 --> 13:54.334
<i>It's now moving east
on Masconomet,</i>

13:54.334 --> 13:55.418
<i>high rate of speed.</i>

13:55.418 --> 13:56.670
<i>Vehicle's turned north
on Fifth,</i>

13:56.670 --> 13:57.629
<i>heading westbound now.</i>

13:57.629 --> 13:58.797
Back on Fifth?

13:58.797 --> 14:03.968
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:03.968 --> 14:06.096
What the hell are they doing?
They're going in circles.

14:06.096 --> 14:07.555
<i>Patrol's lost eyes.</i>

14:07.555 --> 14:10.266
<i>Repeat, Patrol's lost eyes
on the offender vehicle.</i>

14:10.266 --> 14:14.646
<i>Black Taurus.
Plates Edward 271, George 54.</i>

14:14.646 --> 14:17.190
<i>Last seen moving north
on the 1500 of Fifth Street.</i>

14:17.190 --> 14:18.358
<i>All units in the area,
please respond.</i>

14:18.358 --> 14:19.609
Eyes?

14:19.609 --> 14:21.778
Nothing.

14:21.778 --> 14:23.321
Clear.

14:25.281 --> 14:29.411
[siren wailing]

14:29.411 --> 14:30.704
Clear.

14:30.704 --> 14:36.167
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:36.167 --> 14:37.127
Voight!

14:41.756 --> 14:43.258
- You all right?
- I'm good. You?

14:43.258 --> 14:44.551
Let's go.

14:44.551 --> 14:46.886
Police! Get back!

14:46.886 --> 14:48.805
50-21 Henry, got eyes
on the offender vehicle.

14:48.805 --> 14:50.223
It's parked at
the 1600 block of Fifth.

14:50.223 --> 14:51.474
I need cars now.

14:51.474 --> 14:53.727
- Let me see your hands!
<i>- Copy, 50-21 Henry.</i>

14:53.727 --> 14:55.729
<i>Backup en route.</i>

14:55.729 --> 14:56.938
Nice and easy.

14:58.440 --> 14:59.566
Let's go.

14:59.566 --> 15:01.609
Easy! Get out of the car.

15:01.609 --> 15:05.572
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:05.572 --> 15:08.283
Clear.

15:08.283 --> 15:13.913
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:13.913 --> 15:15.165
Get me an ambo.

15:15.165 --> 15:16.374
Ambo now!

15:16.374 --> 15:19.586
I need an ambo
to the 1600 block of Fifth.

15:19.586 --> 15:20.628
<i>Copy. Ambo en route.</i>

15:20.628 --> 15:23.340
Noah, I got you.

15:23.340 --> 15:24.132
Ambulance is coming.

15:24.132 --> 15:26.009
You're gonna be okay.

15:26.009 --> 15:27.677
We got you now.

15:27.677 --> 15:29.721
You're okay.

15:29.721 --> 15:31.431
[siren wailing]

15:31.431 --> 15:34.142
You're okay,
just try to stay with me.

15:34.142 --> 15:36.102
We're almost to the hospital.

15:36.102 --> 15:37.479
Can you hear me, Noah?

15:37.479 --> 15:40.774
[machine beeping]

15:40.774 --> 15:43.443
Can you tell me who did this?

15:43.443 --> 15:44.903
[gasping]

15:44.903 --> 15:49.032
Noah, did you know
the person who hurt you?

15:49.032 --> 15:50.450
Can you tell me
what they look like?

15:50.450 --> 15:52.869
Where they took you?

15:52.869 --> 15:54.579
Can you hear me, Noah?

15:54.579 --> 15:56.289
Can you hear me?

15:56.289 --> 15:57.374
Wood.

15:57.374 --> 15:58.375
Okay.

16:00.293 --> 16:05.382
There were pieces
of wood everywhere.

16:05.382 --> 16:06.383
Wood.

16:06.383 --> 16:08.468
Okay. Okay, good.

16:08.468 --> 16:09.552
That helps.

16:09.552 --> 16:10.887
That helps a lot.

16:10.887 --> 16:15.850
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:15.850 --> 16:17.435
I did that to you?

16:20.313 --> 16:21.523
I'm sorry.

16:21.523 --> 16:23.358
I hurt you too.

16:23.358 --> 16:30.323
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:38.248 --> 16:38.748
- Voight.
- Hey.

16:39.582 --> 16:41.501
How is he?

16:41.501 --> 16:43.086
Not good.

16:43.086 --> 16:47.090
I mean, was stabbed six times,
and he lost a lot of blood.

16:47.090 --> 16:50.301
Doctor thinks the knife
probably missed major arteries.

16:50.301 --> 16:52.846
I mean, we'll know more
when he's out.

16:54.681 --> 16:58.435
There were signs of bindings

16:58.435 --> 17:00.061
on his wrists and ankles.

17:00.061 --> 17:02.397
No signs of sexual assault.

17:04.816 --> 17:07.193
His eyes were stapled open.

17:08.820 --> 17:10.155
And knees and feet?

17:10.155 --> 17:11.322
Not broken.

17:16.536 --> 17:18.038
Anything on the car?

17:18.038 --> 17:20.874
Towing it now,
but it's been altered.

17:20.874 --> 17:23.043
The handle's removed from
the inside and the handles

17:23.043 --> 17:24.961
from the safety
and the trunk were removed too.

17:24.961 --> 17:28.173
- Hmm.
<i>- Sarge, you got ears in?</i>

17:28.173 --> 17:29.341
Yeah, I'm here.

17:29.341 --> 17:30.633
Okay, we got a hit
on the Ford Taurus.

17:30.633 --> 17:32.177
Traced it on PODs.

17:32.177 --> 17:34.679
Traffic cams caught it leaving
an abandoned pallet factory

17:34.679 --> 17:36.056
eight minutes before
Patrol clocked it.

17:36.056 --> 17:37.682
<i>The pallets could
explain the wood pieces</i>

17:37.682 --> 17:39.809
<i>Noah mentioned, Sarge.</i>

17:39.809 --> 17:42.771
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

17:42.771 --> 17:49.903
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:07.439 --> 19:08.565
The place is clear.

19:08.565 --> 19:10.483
No one's here but us.

19:10.483 --> 19:11.943
[sniffs]

19:11.943 --> 19:14.821
That's heavy bleach.

19:14.821 --> 19:16.656
Noah must have
ripped a binding

19:16.656 --> 19:18.450
from the wall to escape.

19:20.243 --> 19:22.871
This place linked to Jones?

19:22.871 --> 19:24.914
No. No links at all.

19:24.914 --> 19:27.709
Yeah.
This doesn't match his MO.

19:27.709 --> 19:29.252
This was planned.

19:29.252 --> 19:32.005
Meticulous.

19:32.005 --> 19:34.549
Someone held Noah here.

19:34.549 --> 19:38.678
Stabbed him so he wouldn't die,
so he'd suffer.

19:38.678 --> 19:40.847
Yeah, certainly doesn't feel
like punishment

19:40.847 --> 19:42.807
for stiffing a dealer.

19:42.807 --> 19:44.976
No, this is something else.

19:44.976 --> 19:52.150
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:54.778 --> 19:56.780
Hey.

19:56.780 --> 19:59.949
[machine beeping steadily]

19:59.949 --> 20:02.369
Noah, you're okay. Hey.

20:02.369 --> 20:04.913
You're safe.
You're in the hospital.

20:04.913 --> 20:06.790
You just got out of surgery.

20:06.790 --> 20:10.001
[groans]

20:12.462 --> 20:13.505
You remember me?

20:16.925 --> 20:17.884
Yeah.

20:17.884 --> 20:19.803
I'm Hank.

20:19.803 --> 20:21.513
I'm police.

20:27.977 --> 20:30.021
Noah, is there anyone
I can call for you?

20:32.273 --> 20:34.734
Okay. That's all right.

20:34.734 --> 20:36.194
Listen,
if you think of someone,

20:36.194 --> 20:39.322
you just let me know, okay?

20:39.322 --> 20:40.615
Hey.

20:44.452 --> 20:45.870
[sobs]

20:45.870 --> 20:48.123
I know this is hard
to talk about,

20:48.123 --> 20:50.625
but I really need your help.

20:52.377 --> 20:54.629
Noah, can you tell me
who did this?

20:54.629 --> 20:57.507
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

20:57.507 --> 20:58.550
I know.

20:58.550 --> 20:59.801
I know it's hard.

20:59.801 --> 21:01.344
It's hard.

21:01.344 --> 21:05.348
I promise, I wouldn't be
asking if I didn't have to.

21:05.348 --> 21:06.975
[crying]

21:06.975 --> 21:08.935
Just tell me who hurt you.

21:08.935 --> 21:14.232
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:14.232 --> 21:18.361
I saw footage
of your abduction, Noah.

21:18.361 --> 21:22.574
My God, you fought like hell.

21:22.574 --> 21:25.660
And you made it out.

21:25.660 --> 21:27.037
It's incredible.

21:27.037 --> 21:30.040
I mean, that is incredible.

21:30.040 --> 21:33.752
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:33.752 --> 21:36.379
I just need a little more
of that strength right now.

21:36.379 --> 21:39.674
[sobbing]

21:39.674 --> 21:41.468
You can do this.
You can talk to me.

21:41.468 --> 21:42.469
I know you can.

21:42.469 --> 21:44.054
No. No.

21:44.054 --> 21:45.055
- Yes, you can.
- No, I can't.

21:45.055 --> 21:46.056
- Okay. Okay.
- Please.

21:46.056 --> 21:47.932
Okay. Okay. Okay.

21:47.932 --> 21:49.809
Hey.

21:49.809 --> 21:51.394
Just stay with me
a little longer.

21:51.394 --> 21:53.980
Just clear one thing up
for me, okay?

21:53.980 --> 21:55.940
Noah.

21:55.940 --> 21:58.068
Can you look at these men?

21:59.778 --> 22:02.489
You just tell me if one of them
is the one who hurt you.

22:02.489 --> 22:09.454
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:20.465 --> 22:22.300
Him? He's the one who hurt you?

22:25.929 --> 22:27.263
Can you look at me?

22:27.263 --> 22:28.765
[sobs]

22:28.765 --> 22:30.767
Noah, it's okay.

22:30.767 --> 22:32.185
You're safe.
- It's him.

22:32.185 --> 22:33.269
- Okay.
- Please.

22:33.269 --> 22:35.021
- Noah, are you sure?
- Please.

22:35.021 --> 22:37.315
[sobbing]

22:37.315 --> 22:40.652
[machine beeping rapidly]
- You'll have to leave.

22:40.652 --> 22:47.659
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:55.709 --> 22:58.169
- Well?
- He's awake. In recovery.

22:58.169 --> 22:59.546
Did he talk?

22:59.546 --> 23:02.716
He ID'd Jones,
but, I mean, it was a fake ID.

23:02.716 --> 23:04.342
It was fake?

23:06.344 --> 23:08.013
Wait, how do you know that?

23:08.013 --> 23:10.682
The kid was traumatized.

23:10.682 --> 23:13.309
He would have said anything
to get me out of that room.

23:13.309 --> 23:14.644
- He said that?
- No.

23:14.644 --> 23:17.272
He was on the verge
of a panic attack.

23:17.272 --> 23:19.941
I think he saw Jones,
recognized him as his dealer,

23:19.941 --> 23:21.484
thought that's what I wanted.

23:21.484 --> 23:23.945
All right, listen.
What hour are we on?

23:23.945 --> 23:26.990
Uh, if we want to hold Jones,
we got to charge him right now.

23:26.990 --> 23:28.158
Wait. I'm sorry.

23:28.158 --> 23:29.242
I-I don't understand
the assumption.

23:29.242 --> 23:31.661
How do we know Noah was lying?

23:31.661 --> 23:32.787
Instinct.

23:32.787 --> 23:33.955
Based on?

23:33.955 --> 23:35.498
Experience,
his body language.

23:35.498 --> 23:36.666
And the fact that
whoever tortured Noah

23:36.666 --> 23:38.835
wasn't some pissed off
drug dealer.

23:38.835 --> 23:40.545
This was sadistic.

23:40.545 --> 23:43.173
Someone got pleasure
out of torturing him.

23:43.173 --> 23:44.674
Okay, that could
still fit with--

23:44.674 --> 23:47.719
It doesn't.

23:47.719 --> 23:50.722
All right, we are missing
something, right?

23:50.722 --> 23:52.182
Someone.

23:52.182 --> 23:54.351
Who in Noah's life
is capable of this harm?

23:54.351 --> 23:57.103
What the hell are we missing?

23:57.103 --> 23:58.646
Hank, wait a second.

23:58.646 --> 24:00.565
Look, I got to talk to Jones
before we release him.

24:00.565 --> 24:02.150
Are you kidding?

24:02.150 --> 24:03.526
He could be escalating.

24:03.526 --> 24:05.695
It's still a possibility.
- Noah was lying.

24:05.695 --> 24:07.489
It was a bad ID.

24:07.489 --> 24:10.575
- Hank!
- I'm not wasting time.

24:10.575 --> 24:12.327
Ugh.

24:12.327 --> 24:14.329
You are hereby released
from custody without charges

24:14.329 --> 24:15.830
as the Chicago Police
Department has found

24:15.830 --> 24:17.540
insufficient grounds
for a criminal complaint

24:17.540 --> 24:18.708
against you.

24:18.708 --> 24:22.128
<i>[apprehensive music]</i>

24:22.128 --> 24:23.797
Please sign here
acknowledging your release

24:23.797 --> 24:25.590
before collecting
your personal belongings.

24:25.590 --> 24:27.384
Yeah,
I'll just take a minute.

24:27.384 --> 24:28.718
- Protocol is--
- One minute.

24:28.718 --> 24:34.766
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:37.477 --> 24:38.895
I know where you deal.

24:38.895 --> 24:41.314
I know who you deal to.

24:41.314 --> 24:43.441
And I have every resource
that I will run at you

24:43.441 --> 24:45.902
until you're doing 20
for trafficking.

24:45.902 --> 24:47.612
Mm-hmm.

24:50.532 --> 24:54.160
Or you just tell me what
you know and I will back off.

24:56.413 --> 24:57.872
What do you know about Noah?

24:57.872 --> 25:00.959
- What do I know?
- Yes.

25:00.959 --> 25:02.669
What do you know
that I'm missing?

25:02.669 --> 25:05.630
<i>[tense music]</i>

25:05.630 --> 25:12.637
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:18.935 --> 25:20.186
I mean, we've dug into
every corner of Noah's life

25:20.895 --> 25:21.938
from Chicago to Marion.

25:21.938 --> 25:23.148
There's just not much there.
- Okay.

25:23.148 --> 25:25.650
Well, what's not much?

25:25.650 --> 25:27.986
This family may have strong
opinions, but they're clean.

25:27.986 --> 25:29.320
There's no priors.

25:29.320 --> 25:30.947
His brother Seth was
the one that gave him

25:30.947 --> 25:33.158
the personal safety alarm
because he was worried

25:33.158 --> 25:35.952
about Noah moving to
a modern day Gomorrah.

25:35.952 --> 25:37.579
We looked into members
of their churches,

25:37.579 --> 25:39.247
friends, classmates, nothing.

25:39.247 --> 25:41.082
National database
came up empty

25:41.082 --> 25:42.834
for other related crimes.

25:42.834 --> 25:44.794
The eyelids,
the stabbing is unique.

25:44.794 --> 25:47.339
Come on, there has got to be
something in Chicago.

25:47.339 --> 25:48.840
Kid's been here for two months.

25:48.840 --> 25:50.342
I did get a hit on that.

25:50.342 --> 25:52.344
He was staying off and on
at a homeless shelter,

25:52.344 --> 25:53.845
a place called
Great Lake House.

25:53.845 --> 25:55.263
Spoke with the supervisor.

25:55.263 --> 25:57.182
Apparently, he kept to himself.
He had no friends.

25:57.182 --> 25:58.683
What, he talked to no one?

25:58.683 --> 26:01.436
Apparently. That's what
the supervisor said.

26:01.436 --> 26:03.396
All right,
history of violence there?

26:03.396 --> 26:06.066
We ran it, ran everyone
who came through the shelter.

26:06.066 --> 26:07.650
Petty theft, possession,

26:07.650 --> 26:09.361
pops of prostitution,
but that's it.

26:09.361 --> 26:11.529
What about the party drugs?

26:11.529 --> 26:13.573
I mean, he buys,
he's using somewhere.

26:13.573 --> 26:15.867
Mm-hmm.
But you know he's not 21 yet.

26:15.867 --> 26:17.452
So we got nothing
from the local bars.

26:17.452 --> 26:19.621
Naturally, we got raves
and underground parties,

26:19.621 --> 26:20.872
but nobody's talking to us.

26:20.872 --> 26:23.208
Could it be random attack?

26:23.208 --> 26:25.210
Stranger abduction?
- Eh.

26:25.210 --> 26:27.212
Sarge, offender matches
every stat for Jones,

26:27.212 --> 26:28.505
down to his shoe size.

26:28.505 --> 26:30.965
Maybe the right answer
is the simple one.

26:30.965 --> 26:32.717
Noah's telling the truth.

26:32.717 --> 26:35.553
[phone buzzes]

26:35.553 --> 26:36.638
You got something?

26:39.474 --> 26:41.393
So please, enlighten me,
Sergeant,

26:41.393 --> 26:44.062
why do I have an ASA
coming into my office

26:44.062 --> 26:46.898
telling me you released
a known violent offender,

26:46.898 --> 26:49.442
one who was just
positively ID'd?

26:49.442 --> 26:50.735
Because I did.

26:50.735 --> 26:52.237
We didn't have a case on him.

26:52.237 --> 26:54.239
My investigators
went back to Noah,

26:54.239 --> 26:56.116
and they found his statement
to be credible.

26:56.116 --> 26:57.158
Is that so?

26:57.158 --> 26:58.702
They also uncovered

26:58.702 --> 27:00.620
one of Jones's
old social media profiles,

27:00.620 --> 27:02.706
and it was filled
with homophobic rants.

27:02.706 --> 27:04.708
Hank, this is motive.

27:04.708 --> 27:05.792
It's why he escalated.

27:05.792 --> 27:07.752
This was a hate crime.

27:07.752 --> 27:11.548
So Noah was the only gay man
that Jones sold drugs to?

27:11.548 --> 27:13.174
It was a false ID.

27:13.174 --> 27:14.968
- You cannot know that.
- Of course I can.

27:14.968 --> 27:16.845
I've seen the look before.

27:16.845 --> 27:19.097
Hell, I've seen it
on my own son.

27:19.097 --> 27:20.849
That child was broken.

27:20.849 --> 27:23.101
He would've ID'd the Pope
to get me out of there.

27:23.101 --> 27:25.061
All right, enough.

27:25.061 --> 27:26.855
You have a credible,
sympathetic witness

27:26.855 --> 27:29.524
with a positive ID
and a repeat violent offender

27:29.524 --> 27:31.276
who has beaten
the system twice.

27:31.276 --> 27:32.569
Yeah,
and he will beat it again

27:32.569 --> 27:34.654
if we arrest him
for a crime he didn't commit.

27:34.654 --> 27:37.615
<i>[tense music]</i>

27:37.615 --> 27:39.492
Hank Voight.

27:41.453 --> 27:43.038
Arrest warrant's
already signed.

27:43.038 --> 27:44.289
Go arrest him.
- Sir, he--

27:44.289 --> 27:45.957
That's a direct order.

27:45.957 --> 27:47.959
You don't act unilaterally.

27:47.959 --> 27:49.586
Arrest him.

27:49.586 --> 27:56.551
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:13.943 --> 28:16.196
- Gun!
- Chicago PD!

28:18.698 --> 28:20.575
Drop your weapon!

28:20.575 --> 28:21.743
He's coming to you.

28:23.620 --> 28:27.165
Don't do it.

28:27.165 --> 28:28.833
Drop the gun.

28:28.833 --> 28:30.251
Y'all think you can frame me?

28:30.251 --> 28:31.670
Don't try me, Jones.

28:31.670 --> 28:33.380
Drop the weapon.

28:33.380 --> 28:34.839
- I didn't do this.
- What did I say?

28:34.839 --> 28:36.091
Put the gun down!

28:36.091 --> 28:42.806
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:42.806 --> 28:44.015
Up high, turn around.

28:44.015 --> 28:45.558
Get them high, turn around.

28:47.227 --> 28:48.812
I didn't do this.

28:50.730 --> 28:52.148
Bring him inside.

28:52.148 --> 28:54.067
- What?
- Inside.

28:54.067 --> 28:56.194
- Taking him to the dist--
- Inside now.

28:56.194 --> 28:57.570
- Yeah.
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.

28:57.570 --> 28:58.863
You're not gonna beat
a confession out of me, cop.

28:58.863 --> 28:59.906
I didn't do jack.

28:59.906 --> 29:01.282
We're just gonna talk.

29:01.282 --> 29:02.701
I'm not talking to you.

29:02.701 --> 29:04.536
Yeah, you are.

29:04.536 --> 29:06.705
You think
we're trying to frame you?

29:06.705 --> 29:08.373
You're right.

29:08.373 --> 29:11.543
CPD is trying to bury you
for this.

29:11.543 --> 29:13.878
You're a dead man walking.
- I didn't do--

29:13.878 --> 29:15.005
I know you didn't.

29:15.005 --> 29:17.382
So shut up and listen.

29:17.382 --> 29:19.384
I'm gonna ask you
some questions

29:19.384 --> 29:21.136
and you're gonna
answer them truthfully

29:21.136 --> 29:22.721
or you're going to end up
in a cell

29:22.721 --> 29:26.016
that you can't get out of this
time, do you understand me?

29:26.016 --> 29:27.350
That was one of the questions.

29:27.350 --> 29:29.436
Do you understand?
- Yeah.

29:31.271 --> 29:33.398
Did you sell to Noah?

29:33.398 --> 29:35.984
- Yeah.
- Good.

29:35.984 --> 29:37.527
For how long?
- A couple months.

29:37.527 --> 29:39.279
- Who did he buy with?
- No one.

29:39.279 --> 29:41.031
He buys alone.
- Every time?

29:41.031 --> 29:42.532
- Every time.
- At Sweeney Park?

29:42.532 --> 29:44.826
Yeah.

29:44.826 --> 29:45.994
Where did he live?

29:45.994 --> 29:48.538
- I don't know.
- Come on!

29:48.538 --> 29:50.248
He's got to have friends,
family,

29:50.248 --> 29:52.959
people he parties with,
a place he crashes.

29:52.959 --> 29:56.212
What am I missing?

29:56.212 --> 29:57.756
Who would want to harm him?

29:57.756 --> 29:59.090
What?

29:59.090 --> 30:01.384
Why do you think I know
more than you?

30:01.384 --> 30:03.386
You should be asking
your own people.

30:03.386 --> 30:04.554
What does that mean?

30:04.554 --> 30:05.847
Police have been
following the kid.

30:05.847 --> 30:07.098
- What?
- Yeah.

30:07.098 --> 30:08.183
For a month,
every time he picked up,

30:08.183 --> 30:09.267
there was a black car
following him.

30:09.267 --> 30:10.769
Was it a--
was it a black Taurus?

30:10.769 --> 30:12.771
I figured it was Narcotics
trying to get me for a--

30:12.771 --> 30:14.773
Was it a black Taurus?

30:14.773 --> 30:16.316
I don't know.

30:16.316 --> 30:18.610
Yeah, maybe, yeah.
- It wasn't the police.

30:18.610 --> 30:20.612
That was the offender
stalking him.

30:20.612 --> 30:23.073
Did you see him?

30:23.073 --> 30:24.657
Did you see his face?

30:24.657 --> 30:26.659
Nah.

30:26.659 --> 30:28.661
I didn't.

30:28.661 --> 30:34.250
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:39.255 --> 30:40.548
Right, there is no way in
hell that the only person

30:41.758 --> 30:44.094
that ever saw this car
is Noah's drug dealer.

30:44.094 --> 30:47.472
There's just not that
many people to ask.

30:47.472 --> 30:49.391
Jones sells in Sweeney Park
on that corner

30:49.391 --> 30:51.685
because it's a dead zone.
There's no cameras.

30:51.685 --> 30:52.811
Tweakers aren't talking.

30:52.811 --> 30:54.521
We don't have the car
on traffic cams.

30:54.521 --> 30:55.563
Come on, anywhere?

30:55.563 --> 30:57.107
Except for the
last two days, no.

30:57.107 --> 30:58.608
It's almost impressive.

30:58.608 --> 31:00.485
Did you get anything
from Noah?

31:00.485 --> 31:02.195
No.

31:02.195 --> 31:03.446
Techs found a burner
at Jones's house.

31:03.446 --> 31:05.156
It pinged it on a tower
near the Dan Ryan

31:05.156 --> 31:06.741
during the time
of the abduction.

31:06.741 --> 31:09.828
Traffic cam confirms
Jones at the wheel.

31:09.828 --> 31:11.996
Alibi's real.

31:14.165 --> 31:16.042
Come on, there's got to be
more on this car.

31:16.042 --> 31:18.003
What else we got?

31:22.924 --> 31:24.926
All right.

31:24.926 --> 31:27.429
All right, it's late.

31:27.429 --> 31:29.889
Just go home, change out,
get some rest.

31:29.889 --> 31:31.099
Get out of here.

31:32.851 --> 31:34.477
- Sarge, I can stick around.
- Hailey, no.

31:34.477 --> 31:35.729
We'll start fresh
in the morning.

31:35.729 --> 31:37.147
Go. Go ahead.

31:37.147 --> 31:40.150
<i>[apprehensive music]</i>

31:40.150 --> 31:47.323
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:35.056 --> 33:36.808
Yeah, that's him.

33:36.808 --> 33:38.601
But like I told
your other officers,

33:38.601 --> 33:41.688
I never saw him with anyone
or saw a car following him.

33:41.688 --> 33:42.939
He's a quiet one.

33:42.939 --> 33:46.276
Did he mention any friends, associates?

33:46.276 --> 33:47.736
Hardly said a word.

33:47.736 --> 33:49.195
I don't think he knew
anybody here.

33:49.195 --> 33:50.780
He mostly slept.

33:51.948 --> 33:52.949
Thanks.

33:52.949 --> 33:55.618
No, I don't remember him.

33:55.618 --> 33:58.621
And I don't remember
ever seeing a car.

33:58.621 --> 34:02.292
Why? Did--did he do something?

34:02.292 --> 34:04.669
Doesn't seem like the type,
does he?

34:04.669 --> 34:06.046
No, he doesn't.

34:06.046 --> 34:09.507
Always had the idea
that he wanted to be alone.

34:09.507 --> 34:11.801
I tried to talk to him
about his singing once.

34:11.801 --> 34:15.138
He was polite, but he clearly
didn't want any conversation.

34:15.138 --> 34:16.181
Singing?

34:16.181 --> 34:17.599
Mm-hmm.

34:17.599 --> 34:19.934
I heard him singing
in the bathroom once.

34:19.934 --> 34:22.020
Gospel.

34:22.020 --> 34:23.730
He has a beautiful voice.

34:25.315 --> 34:27.525
I hope he doesn't lose that.

35:17.075 --> 35:20.036
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

35:20.036 --> 35:26.668
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:29.105 --> 36:31.608
Who the hell are you?

36:47.415 --> 36:49.542
Hey.

36:49.542 --> 36:50.919
No, no, no, no.

36:50.919 --> 36:52.087
It's okay.

36:52.087 --> 36:54.214
Hey.

36:54.214 --> 36:56.299
I'm not gonna ask you anything.

36:56.299 --> 36:59.302
You don't have to talk.

36:59.302 --> 37:01.388
I did want to say some things.

37:01.388 --> 37:02.764
Would that be okay?

37:10.855 --> 37:12.273
First--

37:12.273 --> 37:13.775
first, I want to tell you

37:13.775 --> 37:17.737
that the man you ID'd,
your dealer, Zach Jones,

37:17.737 --> 37:19.447
I mean, his alibi is airtight.

37:19.447 --> 37:22.200
He couldn't have abducted you.

37:22.200 --> 37:23.910
That's okay.

37:23.910 --> 37:25.203
These things happen.

37:25.203 --> 37:30.083
Look, Noah, people
that are scared or in shock,

37:30.083 --> 37:31.292
they make the wrong ID.

37:31.292 --> 37:32.419
Happens all the time.

37:32.419 --> 37:33.962
It's okay.

37:45.724 --> 37:48.393
Noah, you said something to me
in the ambulance.

37:50.478 --> 37:52.397
You said

37:52.397 --> 37:54.733
you thought you hurt me too.

37:57.402 --> 37:59.487
Noah, you didn't hurt me.

37:59.487 --> 38:02.365
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

38:02.365 --> 38:04.576
Did you do something
that caused this?

38:06.202 --> 38:07.203
No.

38:07.203 --> 38:09.873
I didn't think so.

38:12.917 --> 38:16.588
So the only one responsible
is the monster who did this.

38:18.423 --> 38:21.426
And I'm gonna find him.

38:21.426 --> 38:24.637
I promise you,
I am gonna find him.

38:27.849 --> 38:30.769
And I'm gonna be right here
with you in this thing

38:30.769 --> 38:33.563
until you're able to talk
to me, you understand?

38:35.982 --> 38:38.735
You're not alone.

38:38.735 --> 38:42.113
I'm not gonna let you be alone.

38:42.113 --> 38:49.120
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:54.793 --> 38:56.628
Please, just hear me out.

38:56.628 --> 38:59.130
Have a coffee with me
and hear me out?

39:08.056 --> 39:10.767
Jones didn't do it.
You were right.

39:10.767 --> 39:12.811
But because of his arrest,
techs found a hard drive

39:12.811 --> 39:15.146
in his basement,
and it had footage of him

39:15.146 --> 39:16.439
abusing two other victims.

39:16.439 --> 39:17.899
So we've got him on those.

39:17.899 --> 39:19.401
He's going away.

39:19.401 --> 39:20.819
That's good.

39:22.529 --> 39:24.948
Any leads on Noah's abductor?

39:24.948 --> 39:28.827
No, not yet,
but, uh, there will be.

39:30.954 --> 39:32.831
Hank, I'm sorry
I went over your head.

39:34.666 --> 39:36.418
I made the call
I thought was right.

39:36.418 --> 39:38.336
I felt it
that Jones was our guy.

39:38.336 --> 39:40.130
I was sure of it.

39:40.130 --> 39:41.131
Do you know that feeling?

39:41.131 --> 39:42.799
[scoffs]

39:42.799 --> 39:45.885
Hank, it's my job
to be checks and balances.

39:45.885 --> 39:47.679
If it were
the other way around,

39:47.679 --> 39:49.389
I think you would have done
the same thing.

39:49.389 --> 39:51.975
Yeah, you're probably right.

40:01.526 --> 40:03.028
You do this, you know.

40:04.821 --> 40:06.322
You ask me for help,
you bring me in,

40:06.322 --> 40:08.366
and then...

40:08.366 --> 40:11.494
you push me away.

40:11.494 --> 40:14.456
And it's like--

40:14.456 --> 40:15.874
it's like you don't know

40:15.874 --> 40:18.460
whether you want to be alone
on your island or not.

40:18.460 --> 40:25.133
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:26.593 --> 40:29.054
Hi. Sorry.

40:29.054 --> 40:31.681
I don't know where I put the
painkillers from the hospital.

40:31.681 --> 40:33.850
It's been three hours.

40:33.850 --> 40:36.811
Bathroom cupboard,
top shelf.

40:36.811 --> 40:38.730
- Thank you.
- Mm-hmm.

40:44.736 --> 40:46.196
He had nowhere to go.

40:46.196 --> 40:53.161
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:01.711 --> 41:04.631
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

41:04.631 --> 41:11.805
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:31.700 --> 41:34.828
[wolf howls]
